 privatisation, the single market and the environment, and subsidiarity in the development and implementation of devolved and decentralised governance.This book gives new and essential insights for students and practitioners of politics, governance and international relations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPolicy scienceszGreat Britain. 0aPolitical planningzGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144730047240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447300489423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447300489/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013